==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Kynurenic
<hw>Ky`nu*ren"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/, <?/,
dog + <?/ urine.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol. Chem.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to,
or designating, an acid obtained from the urine of dogs. By
decomposition the acid yields a nitrogenous base (called
<xex>kynurin</xex>) and carbonic acid.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>cynurenic</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

